Inside, they utilize tablets at kiosks to upload resumes into the fair database, clutching them in branded folders. Workshops on networking etiquette and an alumni panel discussing preparation for technical interviews occur in adjoining classrooms, with some students rehearsing elevator pitches against the wall. As the final hour approaches, announcement chimes signal ongoing workshops, while a cybersecurity company conducts password-cracking challenges on nearby laptops. As the event concludes, students exit carrying tote bags filled with branded notebooks, pens, and stacks of business cards, while the lingering aroma of coffee and catered snacks fills the air and career center staff log attendance metrics on laptops.
